@@TJvScrollEvStringGrid.DoAfterScroll
Summary
  Responds when the user stops scrolling.
Description
  DoAfterScroll is called automatically when the user stops scrolling. It will trigger the OnAfterHScroll
  or the OnAfterVScroll event, depending on the value of msg.  
Parameters
  msg        - Represents the parameters of the Windows message that informs the grid of the event.
  scrollcode - Specifies a scroll bar value that indicates the user's scrolling request. 
               This can be one of the following values:
                 SB_BOTTOM, SB_ENDSCROLL, SB_LINEDOWN, SB_LINEUP, SB_PAGEDOWN, SB_PAGEUP, 
                 SB_THUMBPOSITION, SB_THUMBTRACK or SB_TOP.
See Also
  DoBeforeScroll, OnAfterHScroll, OnAfterVScroll
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvScrollEvStringGrid.DoBeforeScroll
Summary
  Responds when the user starts scrolling. 
Description
  DoBeforeScroll is called automatically when the user starts scrolling. It will trigger the OnBeforeHScroll
  or the OnBeforeVScroll event, depending on the value of msg.
  
  The result value of DoBeforeScroll is False, if allowScroll is set to False in OnBeforeHScroll or in
  OnBeforeVScroll; otherwise it is True.
Parameters
  msg        - Represents the parameters of the Windows message that informs the grid of the event.
  scrollcode - Specifies a scroll bar value that indicates the user's scrolling request. 
               This can be one of the following values:
                 SB_BOTTOM, SB_ENDSCROLL, SB_LINEDOWN, SB_LINEUP, SB_PAGEDOWN, SB_PAGEUP, 
                 SB_THUMBPOSITION, SB_THUMBTRACK or SB_TOP.
See Also
  DoAfterScroll, OnBeforeHScroll, OnBeforeVScroll
